this bill focuses on public postsecondary education, cross-campus enrollment, and online education at the california state university.ab 386 authorizes any student enrolled at a csu campus who meets specified requirements to enroll, without formal admission, and without payment of additional tuition or fees, except as provided, in a course provided entirely online, as defined, by another csu campus on a space-available basis.a student is qualified to participate in the program established by this chapter if he or she is enrolled at a csu campus and meets the following requirements:the student should have attained a grade point average of 2.0 on a 4-point scale for work completed.each csu campus shall inform students who may enroll in an online course pursuant to this chapter of all of the following:the 23 campuses of the csu system coordinate their online course offerings in order to provide students improved access to coursework and the opportunity to accelerate their degree completion.the host campus may charge participating students a reasonable administration fee and specific course-based fees, not to exceed an amount sufficient for the campus to recover reasonable administrative costs it incurs pursuant to this chapter.an easily accessible online database of online courses is available at all csu campuses. this database shall provide csu students with a streamlined process within the csu system to allow students to find and enroll in courses that will earn them credit toward graduation, general education, and major requirements.phone:408-924-2337email:ecampus@sjsu.edulocation: irc, room 206ecampus, irc206instructional resource centersan jose state universityone washington squaresan jose, ca 95192-0026